parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty ignition switch can cause the engine to cut out, leading to a loss of power and control, which can be dangerous, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: Engine cuts out
loss of power
inability to start the engine
faulty battery charging.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty speedometer can cause the driver to lose awareness of their speed, leading to potential accidents or traffic violations.
symptoms: Speedometer needle sticks or freezes
inaccurate speed readings
speedometer stops working altogether.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning anti-theft system can cause the vehicle to become inoperable, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Vehicle won't start
anti-theft system light on the dashboard pops on and off
requires resetting the system by turning the key to the "on" position for an extended period.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty odometer can make it difficult for the driver to track their mileage, leading to potential maintenance and safety issues.
symptoms: Odometer does not light up properly
unable to see the mileage on the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty headlight can reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: One or both headlights fail to function
poor electrical engineering/manufacturing of the headlight system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hood prop can cause the heavy hood to fall, leading to serious injury or even death.
symptoms: The hood prop bends or collapses
the hood falls while in the open position
the hood is difficult to open or close due to its weight
the hood prop is flimsy or weak.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the back glass hinge can cause the glass to stick up over the back, making it difficult or impossible to open or close, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The back glass hinge comes unglued from the glass
the back glass sticks up over the back
the back glass is difficult or impossible to open or close
the hinge falls down when the glass is opened.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall or die while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies while driving
the "Low Trac" light comes on
the vehicle will not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Condensation in the headlights can reduce visibility while driving, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Water or condensation accumulates inside the headlights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument panel gauges can cause inaccurate readings, including the speedometer and fuel gauge, leading to safety issues such as speeding tickets or running out of gas.
symptoms: The speedometer and fuel gauge needles stick
flutter
or become inoperative
providing inaccurate readings.
